Website - Bhuvan Deltas 
Website URL - https://bhuvan-app1.nrsc.gov.in/deltas/index.php
Website Content Details - 
This Bhuvan Geoportal depicts the indian region delta's characteristics through a range of geo-spatial data , integrated from magnitude sources 
The Bhuvan Deltas application allows users to explore the deltas of India. It provides information on the location, size, and characteristics of each delta. The application also includes data on the hydrology, ecology, and human settlements of the deltas.

The Bhuvan Deltas application is a valuable resource for researchers, students, and anyone interested in learning more about the deltas of India. It provides a comprehensive overview of these important ecosystems.

Here are some of the features of the Bhuvan Deltas application:

Location: The application provides a map of India showing the location of each delta.
Size: The application provides the area of each delta.
Characteristics: The application provides information on the geology, hydrology, ecology, and human settlements of each delta.
Hydrology: The application provides data on the rivers, streams, and wetlands of each delta.
Ecology: The application provides data on the flora and fauna of each delta.
Human settlements: The application provides data on the population, infrastructure, and economic activity of each delta.
The Bhuvan Deltas application is available in English and Hindi. It can be accessed online or through a mobile app.

Here are some specific examples of the information that is available in the Bhuvan Deltas application:

The Mahanadi Delta is the largest delta in India, with an area of over 20,000 square kilometers. It is located in the states of Odisha and Andhra Pradesh. The delta is formed by the confluence of the Mahanadi River and the Bay of Bengal.
The Sundarbans Delta is the largest mangrove forest in the world. It is located in the states of West Bengal and Bangladesh. The delta is formed by the confluence of the Ganges, Brahmaputra, and Meghna rivers.
The Godavari Delta is the third largest delta in India, with an area of over 10,000 square kilometers. It is located in the states of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana. The delta is formed by the confluence of the Godavari River and the Bay of Bengal.
The Bhuvan Deltas application is a valuable resource for anyone interested in learning more about the deltas of India. It provides a comprehensive overview of these important ecosystems.
